data.name: generalInfoTextBox.Text
data.value:
Position in Solar System: Third planet from the Sun
Distance from Sun: Approximately 93 million miles (150 million kilometers)
Orbital Period: Approximately 365.25 days (one Earth year)
Rotation Period: Approximately 24 hours (one Earth day)
Equatorial Diameter: Approximately 12,742 kilometers (7,918 miles)
Surface Area: Approximately 510 million square kilometers (197 million square miles)
Composition: Mostly rock and iron with a thin outer layer of soil and water
Atmosphere: Composed mainly of nitrogen (78%) and oxygen (21%) with traces of other gases
Population: Approximately 7.9 billion people (as of 2022)
Biodiversity: Home to millions of species of plants, animals, and microorganisms
